survey_response.review_text:
I went to sushila matrutva clinic for the pregnancy checkup.Doctor hira is so good.All staff is so helping.

Doctor cleared all my doubts and explained everything very well.

My pregnancy journey went so smooth with her guidance.

Dr. Hira Mardi, no one else can justify this name more than her.
She is truly gem of a person.She is just like an angel for all of us "to be a mother out there". An angel who showers her love sitting in "Sushila Mathrutva Clinic".
Initially, when my husband and I met her she welcomed us with a warm wish for our new journey that we entered.Soon when our routine checkups started with her, she always made us feel homelike on our visits to her clinic.
We never felt as if we are meeting a professional doctor, and we are her patients or clients.She always treated us like a family with that personal touch to make us feel comfortable.Not even this but her clinic staff is also very good.
We are lucky and fortunate to have her as our doctor throughout this journey.
Dr. Mardi is full of life and down to earth as a doctor she has all warmth for her patients.Fortunately my journey of being a mother with her was very comfortable and I did not even realize when my 9 months passed.
I wish her good health, wealth and success in her future endeavors.May she deliver many more babies ahead. As a happy n satisfied patient I highly recommend Dr.Hira Mardi.

Recently, we are blessed with an adorable baby girl.. I'm really glad that we got in touch with Dr. Hira.Mardi from the 1st day of my pregnancy and have been consulting her since last 9 months. This was my1st pregnancy and it was high risk as I had medical complications but because of Dr. Hira Mardi's treatments, availability, caring nature, guidance, and 24/7 availability made my high risk pregnancy very smooth. We wanted normal delivery, and Dr. Hira Mardi did everything in her hands to support my decision. Due to low hemoglobin and other medical complications we had to induce labour 2 weeks early for the safety of our baby. I was in labour for almost 30 hours and Dr. was always there checking on me. I couldn't bare the labour pain n had to switch to c-section.. The operation went really smooth.. we had our baby girl delivered at Cloudnine.  

I highly recommend Dr. Hira Mardi for anyone who is looking for an amazing ObGyn for their pregnancy journey.

We Thank you Doctor from the bottom of our heart for always being there especially during this tough time of covid-19.  Thanks for advising us and explaining each and every minute details, reminding me the importance of having meds/exercise and keeping track of everything during regular checkups. Thank you for always being available and reminding us by texts and calls.
  
We will always be grateful to you🙏

Recently we blessed with an adorable baby girl...We are really fortunate to get in touch with Dr. Hira Mardi during our pregnancy. We have been consulting her since last one year and the experience was so nice that I would recommend her to everyone for any Gynec and obstetrics related issues. Her timely treatments, professional guidance, kind words, caring nature and availability made our voyage of pregnancy very smooth and exciting. Our baby girl was delivered(normal) with supervision of Dr Hira Mardi at Apollo Cradle. As I was there in the labour room during the delivery, I will treasure all those moments that I have witnessed for my entire life. Its hard to express the happiness having a new life in words. 

We Thank you Doctor from the core of our heart for always being there during the pregnancy and delivery of our share of happiness. Thanks for advising us and explaining each and every minute details and keeping track of everything during regular checkups. Moreover as this is our first child, thanks for educating us and being patient to answer all concerns and queries including the silly ones. Thank you for always being available and reminding us by texts and calls whenever I missed the dates.
  
We will always remain grateful to you for this new life of parenthood. We love you mam. Regards.
Doctor Hira was very sincere in her treatment approach and explained the problem very well. She is a very good doctor and trusted medical practitioner.

I am going to provide my feedback for Dr.Hira Mardi based on my personal experience for my second delivery.I was pregnant with 4 months, when we moved from other part of Bangalore to Channasandra as this place is near to my husband office.My husband was searching for a **** doctor near  to us and he found one doctor is available right now in clinic Sushila Mathrutva. So, we decided to go and meet with Dr. Hira once. After our first meeting only, she made us speechless with her attitude and the way she took care of me.Dr. Hira listens all the complexation very carefully I was going through and answered all my questions with smiling. From the beginning she was planning for normal delivery for me even though I had C-section before 3 years back.She improved my health condition by suggesting good medicine and diets. I was feeling always nausea and doing too much vomiting during that period. But Dr. Hira suggested all the precautions.By time I was getting better and my health condition improved with her supervision. At the time when delivery date was near, she was regular taking care of me by checking my health condition. She asked me that I can contact her at any time (24/7) if there is any complexion. Even if she couldn’t pick the call may be due to her busy schedule but immediate next to that she called me back.At the last month we came to know that my baby is in breech position. Even though she gives us hope to wait for last week, in case baby position may change. But it didn’t happened for my case.Now when the date came for delivery, Dr. Hira provided option of some top hospital name where she visits. We choose Apollo Cradle. She did very well C-Section delivery.Finally, Alhumdulillah we blessed with baby girl. Masha Allah!!!.My experience with Dr. Hira Mardi was excellent and was good memory for us.I wish Dr. Hira to get more success and her career and her life and always be same how you have treated me. Thank you Dr. Hira!!.
Dr Hira Mardi she is vary good doctor she will be friendly with patient great doctor . I will suggest to my friend and family to visit clinic. She is great full

What is the point of taking so much money ** *** ***** **** ** ******** ******* ********* ***** when I met her for the follow up, she was on her phone the entire time and was not answering properly any question. How would a patient feel if the doctor is not paying attention? Why do people go to hospitals? To have clarity, right? This doctor only made me and my husband negative about the whole situation. *** **** *** **** ** *** ******* ** ** *** *** ******* *** **** ****** ******* ********* ** ** * **** **** **** *** * **** ********** ** ******* She is so unpleasant that my entire day got wasted  just by visiting her. I had to go to another doctor for the consultation ** ****** ********* *** ******* ****** ****** *** ** **** ****** ***** **** ****** ********* I just feel I wasted my money on her consultation *** *** ****** ********** * *** ** ** ******* *** ** ******.

We got to know about Dr.Hira Mardi from Practo. We have been visiting her clinic (Shushila Mathrutva Clinic) for my wife's pregnancy since Jun'20.Dr. Hira listen to our concerns, takes care of my wife very nicely. She didn't over-burden my wife with too much medications. Her clinic has a USG Facility, which was extremely helpful during Covid time, so we didn't have to roam around to other facilities or hospitals for USG. She is extremely nice person but at the same time very professional. Because of her, my wife went for Normal Delivery, and we are blessed with a healthy baby girl. She did all the procedures. Last but not the least, as being a very nice person, she has been doing a very good service. Her remuneration for consultations and for USG at her facilities are quite reasonable. Her assistants at the clinic were quite helpful.We are glad, we got in touch with Dr.Hira Mardi, as we would be forever thankful.

I had consulted with Dr. Hira for pregnancy, since start till post delivery and we are very much happy and satisfied the way she dealt our case. With proper diagnosis and tests carried out on time we could identify the complications before hand like hypothyroidism, diabetes, urinary tract infections and hence precautions/treatment was done. Doctor is very caring and friendly and explains everything with utmost patience. The clinic is well equipped and I got all the scans and tests done at the same place itself. The staff/sisters are also very responsible, caring and friendly which makes the overall experience excellent. We were blessed with our baby on June 1st, all thanks to Doctor Hira.

I was done with LSCS under her and delivered with an angel. and Iam completely satisfied with Hira mam and her treatment. I had consulted doctor Hira Mardi for my pregnancy. As it was my first pregnancy I had lots of doubts what to do and what not to.I used to ask every single question to the doctor and Hira mam used to answer all my doubts without hesitation even it’s a silly one. She used to explain in detail and creates friendly environment in each and every visit.
As instructed by doctor I used to walk and do exercises due to which I got the contractions naturally in 38th week. Doctor tried for normal delivery for about 15 hours but since the baby passed mecconium we don’t have time to wait for normal delivery. I had c section and delivered a healthy baby.
Overall I would say it’s a great experience with doctor Hira Mardi and I would highly recommend everyone to consult Hera mam to have a healthy and happy pregnancy journey.

So by searching on google I found Dr. Hira Mardi's clinic very close by to my house. The moment we met the doctor we felt very comfortable and the doctor is very friendly, in simple words made our tension and stress go away and instilled confidence that I am there for you even in this covid19 pandemic situation.
My wife has a fibroid in her uterus, still the journey from first meting the doctor to the delivery of the baby went on very smoothly as doctor was available for us at just a phone call away. 
I was tensed as i dint have any relatives here, and due to pandemic was not able to call anyone here, how will I manage, but still due to doctors support and guidance all went well and I am blessed with a baby girl. 
With Dr Hira Mardis reference we got the delivery done at Cloud9 and the experience was very good and pleasant.
